place.name: WYBERTON
place.gazetteerText: WYBERTON, a parish in Boston district, Lincoln; 2¼ miles S of Boston r. station. Post town, Boston. Acres, 3,231. Real property, £8,394. Pop., 608. Houses, 121. The property is much subdivided. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £597.* Patron, Mrs. Dunning. The church is ancient but good. There are a Wesleyan-chapel, and charities £38. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
